This article contains statements from various members of Congress and leaders across the country regarding President Obama's plan for economic growth and deficit reduction. The statements generally express support for the plan, which aims to reduce the budget deficit by more than $4 trillion over the next decade through a combination of spending cuts and tax increases on the wealthy. Many of the statements emphasize the need for shared sacrifice and fairness in addressing the deficit crisis, with some specifically praising the inclusion of the "Buffet Rule," which calls for millionaires to pay a minimum tax rate. The plan also includes provisions to create jobs and strengthen programs like Medicare and Medicaid.